Overview

This document was created to facilitate an easy look up of the actual data used within the publication. All presented tables can be filtered, searched, sorted and downloaded in your desired output format. We hope that this opens the door for easy data reuse!

How to use

This is a html file and can be open within a browser. You can see on the top left the entire content of the document. If clicking on a top potential subcategories will drop out and you can also click on one of those to navigate to the section of interest. The tables display most often entitie-wise information, always annotated with all available information as well. Note that those columns are attached by default to the right of respective table, so you might have to scroll to see those information. You can use drag and drop to reorder the columns (Drag the column header!).

Each column can be searched by typing into the box just underneath each column header. If numerical values are present you can specify to see everything below or above a certain threshold. If you click now on your desired table format to download that certain selection will be downloaded.

If you want to download the entire table you need to check if nothing is selected (default).

Cluster Sets & ORA

counter = 0

#htmltools::tagList(datatable(matrix()))
for(i in names(Transcriptome_CoCena)){
  for(j in names(Transcriptome_CoCena[[i]])){
    counter = counter + 1
      data2show <- Transcriptome_CoCena[[i]][[j]]
      
      customCaption = paste0("Table ",counter,": Cluster: ",i," ",j," enrichment results")
      
      print(htmltools::tagList(DT::datatable(
        data2show,
         caption = customCaption,
        extensions = c('Buttons','ColReorder'),
        filter = 'top',
        options = list(
          paging = TRUE,
          searching = TRUE,
          fixedColumns = TRUE,
          colReorder = TRUE,
          autoWidth = TRUE,
          ordering = TRUE,
          dom = 'Bfrtip',
          buttons = c('copy', 'csv', 'excel')
        ),
        class = "display"
      ))
      )
  }
}
